RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRANDDADDYLONGLEGS stalked the early speed from just outside, took over with two furlongs to go, drew off in the lane while kept to urging until the final sixteenth. CHARLIE'S BEACH without early speed, saved ground, rallied two wide in the lane and split horses inside the final sixteenth to take over second. FLYING CRICKET in contention from outside, floated out to path five entering the stretch, moved clear for second but could not sustain his bid late. LONE RETURN chased from outside, angled in through the turn, took over third along the rail upper stretch then leveled off in the waning yards. UH OH IT'S MAGIC chased two or three wide and had no late bid. UNDEFEATED CHAMP displayed early speed from inside, was overtaken with a quarter mile left, floated out to path four entering the lane and steadily gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRAGGING MAIN soon had a clear lead, showed the way in hand from inside, was let out some into the second turn, under a drive through the lane and was clearly the best. HOT CUPPA COFFEE prompted the pace from just off the inside, fanned out some for the stretch run, gradually drifted out as he pulled away for second and held a straight path the final sixteenth. CHERRY ORCHARD gradually closed the gap from outside on the backstretch, moved clear for third three wide on the second bend, stayed outside HOT CUPPA COFFEE into the lane, altered inside that one with a furlong to go, steadily lugged in after that and narrowly held on for the show. RED ROIL bore in some just after the break, was settled inside, picked up his pace after a half mile, saved ground taking the second turn, altered out for a clear path just after entering the last eighth and was closing in for third late. TEMPLE FOOL hesitated at the start, progressed from inside, came off the rail some for the drive, altered in as CHERRY ORCHARD came close inside the last eighth and was checked behind that one in the waning yards. GOD GUNS N GUTS chased while toward the outside, came into the stretch from path five and had no late bid. LELAND JOHN raced in the second flight from outside but gave way from between rivals with three furlongs to go. There was a stewards' inquiry into TEMPLE FOOL'S loss of action deep stretch and the rider of TEMPLE FOOL lodged an objection claiming interference from CHERRY ORCHARD nearing the wire. After their review, the stewards disqualified CHERRY ORCHARD and placed him fifth.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Cherry Orchard
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 wide, altered in 1/8, gradually lugged in, held 34d

ENTRY.NAME: Hot Cuppa Coffee
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path 2nd turn, gradually drifted out stretch, easily 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Dragging Main
ENTRY.COMMENT: clearly best, driving

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, altered out inside 1/8, mild bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BERTRADA rated off the early speed, commenced her bid along the rail on the turn, got through inside MY LADY SLEW into the lane, moved clear and maintained full control under steady handling. PALAGO shared the lead outside MY LADY SLEW from the early going, came into the stretch from path three, battled the latter for second and edged ahead for the place the final seventy yards. MY LADY SLEW disputed the pace off the rail but inside her rival, saved ground on the bend, floated out some entering the stretch, fought to keep second but did not have enough late. ROCK THE BIRDHOUSE without early speed, also saved ground taking the turn and rallied belatedly the final furlong. WAR COLORS hesitated at the break, was hustled up between rivals, reached contention two wide on the bend, fanned out some entering the lane, altered out for a clear path midstretch, had every chance but leveled off in the waning yards. ZENCHUA SKY soon trailed, stayed widest of all and had no significant stretch response.

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, closing

ENTRY.OWNER: Morgan Sharon R and Warchol Thoroughbreds LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated start,2-3 path turn,altered out midstretch,evenly late

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, got thru inside into stretch, driven clear

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside turn, 2-path into stretch, dueled for 2nd, weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: outside trip, no threat

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 2-3 path turn, dueled for 2nd, edged ahead late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE OF MAYHEM quickly moved clear and took the inside, lengthened his lead while in hand on the backstretch, was roused with two furlongs to go and maintained full control under steady urging in the stretch. SUPER SILVER was away slowly, gradually progressed from inside, began to angle out nearing the quarter pole, came into the stretch from path three, drew clear for second, could not close the gap on the leader but was unchallenged for the place. CHERNYAHOVSKIY raced in the second flight from just off the rail, was caught in tight quarters approaching the quarter pole, shuffled back, stayed just off the inside as he gained third entering the stretch and began to wear down the final furlong. CAMPAIGN SPY gradually progressed from outside to gain a striking position four wide midway on the second bend but leveled off for the drive. CHANGE DIRECTION void of speed, though urged along early, chased from just off or along the rail, swung out widest for the stretch run and failed to have a significant response. GAGOOTS soon trailed, was also just off or along the rail and had little to offer in the lane. SHOBIZ STAR in the second flight early just outside CHERNYAHOVSKIY, was also in close quarters between rivals nearing the quarter pole and gave way soon after that.

ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, middle move inside, angled out 1/4, best of rest

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight 2 wide, shuffled back 1/4, weakened stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEN RESPONSE bumped with MY KINDA TETON at the start, was settled just off the inside, picked up his pace after a half mile, split rivals two wide on the second turn, fanned to path four into the lane, brushed with UNCLE O. G. upper stretch, vied for the lead from outside soon after and edged ahead in time. PAYNT BY LETTERS vied for the lead from outside from the beginning, was four wide taking the first bend, angled in beside UNCLE O. G. on the backstretch, moved clear on the second turn, was challenged from both sides upper stretch, fought gamely the last furlong but had to settle for second best. MARCHING ORDERS settled from inside, also commenced his bid after a half mile, steadily progressed to vie for the lead upper stretch but gradually wore down inside the last eighth. MY KINDA TETON bumped with KEEN RESPONSE at the break, chased from outside, lost ground five wide on the second bend, angled in some entering the lane, gained a striking position, altered out some for a clear path inside the last eighth and failed to have the needed late kick. THACKER FROMM chased from between rivals, lost ground four to six wide taking the second turn, reached contention upper stretch, lugged in with a furlong to go and leveled off. UNCLE O. G. shared the early lead from inside, did not stay with PAYNT BY LETTERS on the second bend, swung out to path three for the drive, was crowded briefly by KEEN RESPONSE upper stretch and gradually yielded between rivals. RIP IT RYAN reluctant to load, turned his head just as the gate opened, chased from just off the inside, angled out widest in the stretch and had little to offer. SAFE chased the early speed from path three, fanned out five wide into the lane, altered in trying to stay clear of THACKER FROMM near the eighth marker, was checked when his path disappeared with a furlong to go, altered out awkwardly and steadily faded. LORD SHAFTESBURY displayed brief speed between rivals, did not stay close while just off the rail on the backstretch, quit after a half mile and was allowed to coast through the stretch. There was a stewards' inquiry into the stretch run but no action was taken after review.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLOEY ATTACK pressed the early speed from just outside, was all out in the stretch, gained the advantage with sixty yards to go, was bumped near the wire but held sway. COOGAN broke a step slow and inward, bumping MISS TENA MARIE, was hustled along from outside, lost ground four wide through the bend, rallied the final furlong, vied for the lead with seventy yards left, lugged in some nearing the wire, bumped CLOEY ATTACK and came up short. SAPPHIRE NIGHTS broke alertly and soon had the inside, floated out some for the stretch run, widened command but began to wear down inside the last eighth. MISS TENA MARIE bumped from the rear at the break, raced in contention three wide but lacked the needed stretch rally.

Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claimin g Price $4,000 (Claiming Races For $3,200 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMFORT ME NOW broke on top, was rated on the front end, let out leaving the second bend, lengthened his lead under urging upper stretch then maintained control while ridden out the last eighth. IRISH DECLARATION advanced from outside on the backstretch, was three wide taking the second turn, all out as he closed the gap on the lead the final furlong and was clearly second best. KARAYEL lugged in some to brush with GO FOR SHERRIE after the start, raced in contention just off the inside, but flattened out for the drive. ZARMAE moved to the outside on the backstretch, stayed in path four through the second bend and had no late bid. GO FOR SHERRIE crowded shortly after the break, was hustled along early, gave way from inside with more than three furlongs to go, coasted in the lane, was eased late and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIGHT ON RICHIE soon had a clear clear, showed the way from inside, was roused on the second bend, floated out to path three for the stretch run, steadily opened up on the rest and was kept to task to the wire. MILLARD'S SMILE settled early, commenced his bid along the rail after a half mile, squeezed through two wide entering the lane and got up for second deep stretch. NULLARBOR raced closest to RIGHT ON RICHIE from just off the inside, fanned outside the latter into the stretch, was no match for RIGHT ON RICHIE and began to wear down inside the last furlong. EMPTY HOLSTER void of speed, though hustled along after the break, tried to progress between rivals after a half mile, was steadied while boxed in behind COPPER CROSSING nearing the second bend, angled out through that turn, came five wide into the stretch, fought for third then leveled off in the late going. ROCKET HOTSHOT bumped with TROY OUNCE at the start, soon trailed, picked up his pace just off the rail after four furlongs, altered out four wide upper stretch and advanced belatedly between horses. LONESOME DREAM was a brief contender from inside, did not keep up on the backstretch, moved clear for third on the second bend, drifted out slightly upper stretch, brushed with MILLARD'S SMILE and gradually faded. COPPER CROSSING chased midpack from inside, angled out on the second turn, came four wide into the lane and had no late bid. STORM BORN advanced from outside on the first bend but began to fade before finishing a half mile. TROY OUNCE bumped with ROCKET HOTSHOT at the break, was hustled up to race in contention outside NULLARBOR but gave way between horses on the second turn.
